commit.message:
Resolve test warnings

This resolves #82. The code in that MR worked but it produced warnings
in the current default lts for the project. I used the qualified import
trick to resolve the warning. Then the partial matches started failing
in newer GHC versions so I resolved that too. This now builds without
warnings on the project LTS, the newest LTS and nightly.

commit.message:
Switch from RetryPolicy to RetryPolicyM

It seems like the RetryPolicy type alias can sometimes cause problems
with type paramter scope in GHC 9. It doesn't really buy us much so we
might as well use the most flexible option.

This is for #71

commit.message: Prepare 0.8.1.2
Update matrix to support latest lts, allow nightly to fail

Set lower bound for base

We've gotten reports that we're no longer compatible with bases < 4.8.
Prepare 0.8.1.1

Remove upper bound on ghc-prim

If there are issues with this down the line they should manifest as
compile-time errors and we can deal with them. I'd prefer to not have
to keep bumping this upper bound.
Prepare 0.8.1.0
